-- AMD says to cut global workforce by 9 percent
-- 
-- Fri Jan 16, 2009 12:57pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/01/16/us-amd-sb-idUSTRE50F5KO20090116

 

 (Reuters) - Advanced Micro Devices Inc says it will reduce "product company" global workforce by about 9 percent. AMD says reduction will be combination of attrition, divestiture of handheld business and an additional headcount cut of about 900 positions. 

 * Says executive chairman Hector Ruiz and CEO Dirk Meyer will take temporary reduction of 20 percent in base salary